  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240ºC/ 220ºC (fan)/ gas 9</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Before you start cooking, take your<strong> steak[s] </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let them adjust to room temperature</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> in half, lengthways, then score the cut side in a criss-cross pattern, taking care not to cut all the way through</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1683722324942-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1683722324942-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1683722324942-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1683722324942-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1683722324942-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>halved potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12 min, then drain and rinse with <strong>cold water</strong> to cool them slightly (reserve the pot!)</p><p>Reboil half a kettle</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1683722337911-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1683722337911-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1683722337911-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1683722337911-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1683722337911-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are boiling, peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Line a baking tray (or two!) with <strong>baking paper </strong>and add the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Mix everything together until fully combined, being careful not to spread the mixture out too thin – this is your <strong>Italian cheese & garlic base</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1683722342852-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1683722342852-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1683722342852-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1683722342852-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1683722342852-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pat the <strong>rump steak[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper and season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>on both sides</p><p>Once cooked and slightly cooled, add the <strong>boiled potatoes</strong> to the <strong>Italian cheese & garlic base</strong>, cut side down</p><p>Drizzle over a little <strong>olive oil</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and put the tray[s] in the oven for 18-20 min or until the potatoes and cheese are golden and crispy</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1683722348196-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1683722348196-x400.jpg",
