          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1683722348196-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, return the reserved pot to a medium heat with 220ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[290ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[430ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>red wine paste </strong>and<strong> beef stock mix </strong>with 3 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[4 1/2 tsp]</span><strong> </strong><span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until reduced by half to a sauce-like consistency, then stir through a large knob of <strong>cold</strong> <strong>butter </strong>– this is your <strong>red wine jus</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1683722352166-x200.jpg",
